### Issue description

Hello üëã

I'm working on a monorepository project. That's mean I have only one huge package.json with a 2Gb `node_modules` directory.
To optimize the size of my apps, which are running on AWS Lambda, I'm building it with `esbuild`.

In most of cases, I have no any NPM module needed in production.
But, I'm still needing the `devDependencies` to build and run serverless commands on my CI/CD.

First of all, I'm installing the dependencies. Then, I'm copying it into the builded app directory. Finaly, I'm running `serverless` commands to package and deploy the app.

The issue is the `sls package` is producing an heavy `.serverless` package: all dependencies are present into this package (+2Gb).

Despite the `excludeDevDependencies` set to `true` and an empty `dependencies` attribute into the `package.json`, all the content of `node_modules` is included into the `.serverless` package.

`my-app/package.json`:
```json
{"name":"my-app","version":"0.0.1","main":"./index.cjs","devDependencies":{},"dependencies":{}}
```
File tree:
```text
- index.js
- node_modules
- package.json
- serverless.base.ts
- serverless.ts
```

How to fix this issue ?

### Service configuration (serverless.yml) content
`serverless.base.ts`:
```typescript
