@DilLip-Chowdary-Codes It's actually per design

If you want to avoid surprises with CF-based deployment, you should apply all changes to resources via CF deployments. Otherwise, things are likely to go out of sync, and you'll get unexpected results like this.

In your specific case, the CF engine didn't notice any changes in environment variables configuration between two CF deployments (it doesn't inspect resources to confirm if they reflect the state of the previous deployment), so in result environment variables were not restored.

